# Vision-Language Models for Urban Digital Twins

This repository contains a prototype system for enriching urban digital twins using mobile crowdsensing, object-detection metadata, geospatial coordinates, and vision-language model interpretation.

## Overview

The system captures street-level images with GPS metadata, processes them using object-detection outputs and a vision-language model, and visualizes the resulting semantic observations in an interactive geospatial dashboard.

## Main Components

- Mobile sensing data: images, GPS, timestamp, and detection metadata
- Vision-language interpretation: semantic enrichment of urban scenes
- Geospatial structuring: GeoJSON-based observation records
- Front-end visualization: Mapbox GL JS dashboard
- Digital twin integration: spatially referenced semantic urban observations

## Methodology

1. Data acquisition from mobile sensors
2. Object-detection metadata extraction
3. Vision-language model interpretation
4. Spatial structuring and storage
5. Interactive digital twin visualization

## Technologies

- Python
- OpenAI Responses API
- Mapbox GL JS
- GeoJSON
- HTML, CSS, JavaScript

## Notes

API keys are not included in this repository. Create a `.env` file based on `.env.example`.
